WEBVTT

00:08.327 --> 00:11.282
lt occurred to me l think we should try
to keep this quiet from Daphne.

00:11.498 --> 00:13.740
- Keep what quiet?
- We got married.

00:14.293 --> 00:17.413
Daphne, are you saying
that you have feelings for Niles?

00:17.630 --> 00:19.006
l think l do.

00:19.215 --> 00:21.885
You can't tell Niles all this.
He says he's happy with Mel.

00:22.094 --> 00:23.802
She says she's happy with Donny.

00:23.971 --> 00:25.799
But l'm not sure l believe
either one of them.

00:25.974 --> 00:28.644
Just remember, Fras, there are
two marriages on the line here.

00:28.852 --> 00:29.932
l'll get a divorce

00:30.104 --> 00:32.560
- and you can call off the wedding.
- l can't.

00:32.732 --> 00:36.861
Donny is a dear and wonderful man,
and l made a promise to him.

00:37.071 --> 00:40.156
l'm sorry. My mind's made up.

00:40.992 --> 00:45.490
Hello. l was wondering
if you might be free for a date.

00:45.706 --> 00:47.865
NlLES:
My God, yes.

00:48.794 --> 00:50.454
There's plenty of time for that later.

00:50.629 --> 00:52.338
Let's get this bloody boat moving.

00:52.548 --> 00:54.126
What--?

00:55.927 --> 00:58.501
- l can't believe this.
- Neither can l.

00:58.681 --> 01:01.848
- What made you change your mind?
- My little niece, Audrey, the flower girl.

01:02.018 --> 01:03.264
She looked up and me and said:

01:03.437 --> 01:05.096
''You're the saddest bride
l've ever seen.''

01:05.272 --> 01:09.567
l figured who was l kidding if l couldn't
fool a 4-year-old with an eye patch.

01:10.195 --> 01:13.280
Remind me to give her a car
for her preschool graduation.

01:14.742 --> 01:17.863
The next thing l knew l was climbing
out of the window of the loo.

01:18.080 --> 01:20.203
You mean you didn't tell Donny?

01:20.416 --> 01:22.160
l didn't tell anyone.

01:22.335 --> 01:24.162
Can't you get this thing moving
any faster?

01:24.379 --> 01:28.592
Well, l would, but we have
to watch out for speed...bumps.

01:29.677 --> 01:31.552
l've never done anything this crazy.

01:31.722 --> 01:33.264
Are you nervous?

01:33.474 --> 01:35.550
Only that l'm gonna wake up.

01:35.977 --> 01:37.140
[CELL PHONE RlNGlNG]

01:37.312 --> 01:38.391
Don't answer it.

01:38.563 --> 01:41.233
lt's probably your brother
wondering if you've seen me.

01:41.400 --> 01:42.563
Maybe it's Mel wondering why

01:42.735 --> 01:45.025
it's taken me half an hour
to put on insect repellent.

01:47.908 --> 01:49.533
Good.

01:53.499 --> 01:55.077
Here we are.

01:55.710 --> 01:57.916
The end of the driveway.

02:02.259 --> 02:03.754
Which way shall we go?

02:03.928 --> 02:07.796
Well, to the right is Seattle
and to the left, l guess, is Canada.

02:08.893 --> 02:12.060
- Any thoughts?
- What's left for us in Seattle?

02:12.230 --> 02:14.472
Ex-wives and ex-fiancÃ©,

02:14.650 --> 02:18.102
a tangled mess of bitterness
and hurt feelings.

02:18.321 --> 02:21.738
Yes, but an excellent symphony
and world-class dining.

02:22.993 --> 02:27.158
Then there's Canada, a fresh start.
A chance for adventure.

02:27.332 --> 02:29.076
Grizzly bears.

02:29.251 --> 02:30.580
[CELL PHONE RlNGlNG]

02:30.753 --> 02:34.170
l don't care. Just pick one. Let's go.

02:34.883 --> 02:37.588
- Maybe we should--
- No. We can't think about that.

02:38.137 --> 02:41.554
l've just ran out on my wedding.
l can't go back.

02:41.725 --> 02:43.599
l need you to be strong.

02:43.769 --> 02:46.177
For you,
l have the strength of Hercules.

02:48.000 --> 02:54.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:55.492 --> 02:56.655
l love you.

02:56.868 --> 02:58.778
And l love you.

02:59.997 --> 03:02.037
[CELL PHONE RlNGlNG]

03:02.959 --> 03:04.454
They're not going away, are they?

03:05.004 --> 03:06.961
lf you wanna keep going, l'll go.

03:07.673 --> 03:09.049
No.

03:09.217 --> 03:12.053
We better go back
and face the music.

03:12.221 --> 03:13.466
We should make things right.

03:14.557 --> 03:15.672
Okay.

03:17.519 --> 03:19.845
All right, all right.
We're on our way back.

03:20.022 --> 03:21.730
Excuse me?

03:21.899 --> 03:24.854
No, there is no Wendell Fong here.

03:26.822 --> 03:29.029
This is gonna be frigging awful.

03:29.242 --> 03:31.614
Well, maybe.

03:31.787 --> 03:33.530
Maybe not.

03:33.706 --> 03:36.244
Sometimes you build these things
up in your mind

03:36.417 --> 03:39.704
and they turn out
not half as bad as you thought.

03:40.297 --> 03:45.340
That being said, l guess
there's no easy way to tell you this.

03:45.595 --> 03:48.680
l'm in love with Niles
and l can't marry you.

03:48.849 --> 03:49.881
[DONNY GROANS]

03:50.059 --> 03:52.136
Donny, are you all right?

03:52.395 --> 03:53.475
[THUD]

03:53.647 --> 03:55.023
DAPHNE:
Donny!

03:55.691 --> 03:58.609
Mel, did you hear what l just said?

04:00.113 --> 04:03.317
Say something. Anything.

04:03.492 --> 04:05.532
[MEL SCREAMlNG]

04:13.046 --> 04:14.706
Wow.

04:22.975 --> 04:24.517
Wow.

04:28.023 --> 04:30.431
Anyone try those little crab cakes?

04:31.819 --> 04:34.108
- What? They were good.
FRASlER: All right, Dad.

04:34.322 --> 04:35.567
We've just had front-row seats

04:35.741 --> 04:38.576
for what is arguably
the most disastrous wedding in history.

04:39.745 --> 04:42.581
We can't just ignore it
with a lot of inane chitchat.

04:45.377 --> 04:47.371
Did you try that mustard dip
that went with them?

04:47.547 --> 04:49.955
- lt was good.
- Niles.

04:50.175 --> 04:52.252
Frankly,
l'd prefer a little inane chitchat

04:52.428 --> 04:54.504
to talking about
what actually happened back there.

04:55.014 --> 04:57.850
Poor Donny.
l've never seen him so upset.

04:58.060 --> 05:00.848
l just wish l'd broken the news to him
in a carpeted room

05:01.022 --> 05:03.478
instead of the rock garden.

05:05.861 --> 05:07.653
l just can't help feeling
that our happiness

05:07.822 --> 05:09.898
has come at the expense
of Mel and Donny.

05:10.075 --> 05:11.984
Yeah,
there was no easy way out of this.

05:12.161 --> 05:13.821
You guys did the right thing
coming back,

05:13.996 --> 05:15.407
l'm proud of you both.

05:15.581 --> 05:17.206
Thanks, Dad.

05:17.375 --> 05:20.330
And thank you, Frasier.

05:20.546 --> 05:23.251
As painful as it was back there,
we owe you a debt of gratitude.

05:23.424 --> 05:25.963
Daphne and l are here now
because of you.

05:26.178 --> 05:28.420
[CHUCKLlNG]
Please, Niles.

05:28.597 --> 05:29.973
l didn't really do all that much.

05:30.141 --> 05:35.219
Just a minor pluck of Cupid's bow.

05:35.898 --> 05:38.306
Nonsense.
You set this whole thing in motion.

05:38.485 --> 05:41.819
Stop it. l'm blushing. Ha, ha, ha.

05:41.989 --> 05:46.118
Just seeing you two kids together
is thanks enough for me.

05:46.328 --> 05:50.196
Although l wouldn't turn down
a bottle of '82 Latour.

05:51.584 --> 05:54.040
- He's not kidding.
- l know.

05:54.212 --> 05:57.499
Oh, look. lsn't that my Winnebago
pulling out from the gas station?

05:57.675 --> 05:58.920
l'd say so.

05:59.135 --> 06:01.128
Dad, l'm amazed
you'd let Simon drive that thing.

06:01.346 --> 06:04.348
Oh, it'll be fine. l gave him
a lecture about drinking and driving.

06:04.892 --> 06:08.060
He did understand
you were discouraging it?

06:08.271 --> 06:10.265
Of course.

06:11.359 --> 06:12.770
Uh-oh.

06:14.362 --> 06:16.984
l just hope he gets my family
to the airport on time.

06:17.157 --> 06:19.649
l wouldn't want them to miss
their plane, if you get my drift.

06:19.827 --> 06:22.782
Yeah, it's them, all right. lt's all
your brothers waving from the back.

06:22.956 --> 06:24.415
DAPHNE: Hello.
- Hey, how you doing?

06:24.583 --> 06:26.208
- Hello.
- See you.

06:26.377 --> 06:29.248
- Oh, well, that's very nice.
- Ohh...

06:29.923 --> 06:33.258
Living up to the Moon
family name, l see.

06:39.685 --> 06:41.310
DAPHNE:
Did Simon get you home all right

06:41.479 --> 06:42.974
after dropping my family
at the airport?

06:43.148 --> 06:45.224
Oh, yeah. He entertained
the whole neighbourhood

06:45.401 --> 06:48.236
trying to parallel park
the Winnebago.

06:48.446 --> 06:51.697
The highlight was when he flattened
a whole row of newspaper racks.

06:51.909 --> 06:54.234
How many did he get?
My record's five.

06:55.121 --> 06:58.158
l suppose he followed that up
with some sort of clumsy advance.

06:58.333 --> 07:02.083
Oh, he tried, but l told him to get lost.
Then he hit on my babysitter.

07:02.255 --> 07:05.672
She showed him why she's the star
of her JV soccer team.

07:06.218 --> 07:08.507
You know, Mum claims
he was dropped as a child.

07:08.679 --> 07:10.340
l think he was thrown.

07:11.975 --> 07:14.763
l can't thank you enough for helping
me return these wedding gifts.

07:14.937 --> 07:16.052
l've been dreading it.

07:16.272 --> 07:18.846
Just reminds me of how many people
l've disappointed.

07:19.943 --> 07:22.613
Daph, you really outdid yourself
on these corn muffins today.

07:22.780 --> 07:28.286
They're light, moist, corny.

07:28.496 --> 07:30.654
He's just being so sweet to me
because of all of this.

07:30.873 --> 07:33.032
No, l mean it. They're delicious.

07:33.251 --> 07:35.043
He hates them. Watch this.

07:35.212 --> 07:38.130
You know, if you finish those off,
l'll make another batch.

07:38.341 --> 07:40.714
l'll fill the freezer.
We can have them with every meal.

07:40.928 --> 07:42.422
All right, all right, l give.

07:42.596 --> 07:45.551
l was just trying to do
something nice around here.

07:47.269 --> 07:50.436
Now, that's the last of it.
Look sharp, Daphne.

07:50.606 --> 07:52.017
[GLASS BREAKS]

07:52.191 --> 07:53.354
DAPHNE:
Simon, you idiot.

07:53.568 --> 07:56.985
Oh, don't get your knickers in a twist.
l already dropped it in the elevator.

07:57.865 --> 07:59.526
l think you've helped enough
for one day.

07:59.701 --> 08:02.323
- Simon, how about a little breakfast?
- Oh, no, thanks, Martin.

08:02.496 --> 08:04.572
l've already had a lovely,
crispy, golden waffle

08:04.749 --> 08:07.916
and a foamy cappuccino
down in the Winnebago.

08:08.086 --> 08:09.878
What? The Winnebago?

08:10.089 --> 08:12.841
That doesn't have a waffle iron
or a cappuccino maker.

08:13.051 --> 08:16.337
Wait, these gifts look like they've been
unwrapped and then wrapped again.

08:18.265 --> 08:20.305
- Simon.
- Know what that is, Daphne?

08:20.476 --> 08:22.054
That's a bread maker.

08:22.270 --> 08:23.848
Which you did not register for.

08:24.022 --> 08:26.229
Some people
are so bloody thoughtless.

08:26.442 --> 08:27.557
[DOORBELL RlNGS]

08:27.735 --> 08:29.978
That's stealing.
These gifts are going back.

08:30.197 --> 08:32.770
Never. Returning
used merchandise is unethical.

08:32.950 --> 08:36.071
And l, for one,
would never be party to it.

08:49.763 --> 08:51.423
So...

08:53.017 --> 08:55.057
Returning wedding presents,
l take it.

08:55.228 --> 08:57.351
That's one problem Mel
and l avoided by eloping.

08:57.522 --> 09:00.228
No presents to return when, uh...

09:00.818 --> 09:02.312
When you shag
someone else's wife?

09:02.528 --> 09:03.987
DAPHNE:
Simon.

09:06.033 --> 09:09.237
- Would you like some coffee?
- l'd love some. Here, let me help.

09:09.620 --> 09:11.827
Ooh. Dad, those look good.
What are they?

09:11.998 --> 09:14.537
- Doorstops.
- Thank you.

09:24.180 --> 09:26.090
- How did you sleep last night?
- l didn't.

09:26.266 --> 09:27.808
- How about you?
- Not a wink.

09:28.018 --> 09:30.391
Um, you know, as pleasant as it was

09:30.563 --> 09:33.055
riding up and down
that driveway yesterday,

09:33.233 --> 09:35.191
l think it hardly qualifies as a date,

09:35.361 --> 09:36.855
so l have a surprise for you.

09:37.405 --> 09:40.193
l made reservations for tonight
at Au Pied de Cochon.

09:40.367 --> 09:43.534
Then after, we're going dancing
at the Starlight Room.

09:43.704 --> 09:46.741
lt'll be our first official date.
You free?

09:46.958 --> 09:49.331
This is awfully short notice.
Can l get back to you?

09:49.545 --> 09:51.087
Yeah, of course.

09:51.255 --> 09:53.332
[LAUGHlNG]
Of course, l'm free, you silly sausage.

09:53.508 --> 09:56.344
- Well--
- lt sounds wonderful.

09:57.012 --> 09:59.586
Um, Daphne-- Uh--

10:00.809 --> 10:02.517
--about us.

10:02.728 --> 10:05.480
l think we shouldn't
rush into anything,

10:05.648 --> 10:09.563
like living together
or even physical relations,

10:09.736 --> 10:14.814
until l have the situation
resolved with Mel.

10:14.993 --> 10:17.116
Do you have any thoughts
about that?

10:17.287 --> 10:19.031
l'm so relieved.

10:19.206 --> 10:21.164
l feel exactly the same way.

10:21.334 --> 10:24.419
We need to get to know each other
in this whole new light first.

10:24.630 --> 10:27.335
- We're completely simpatico.
- Yes.

10:34.642 --> 10:36.719
Although, you know,
in some respects,

10:36.895 --> 10:39.268
we're much further ahead
than most couples.

10:39.440 --> 10:41.480
l already know how you take
your coffee.

10:41.651 --> 10:43.560
Cream. One sugar.

10:43.737 --> 10:45.777
And two lips.

10:45.948 --> 10:47.228
FRASlER:
Good morning.

10:47.408 --> 10:50.363
Mm. Good morning.
No, l don't see anything in your eye.

10:50.996 --> 10:52.075
FRASlER:
For God's sake.

10:52.289 --> 10:55.659
l've got news for you,
the cat is out of the bag.

10:55.835 --> 10:56.914
Well, l'm sorry.

10:57.086 --> 11:00.503
l guess l'm just not used to kissing
the boss's brother in the kitchen.

11:00.674 --> 11:02.667
Not that l'm used to kissing him
any other place.

11:02.844 --> 11:06.296
- l mean any other room.
- Yes, Daphne, l know what you mean.

11:06.640 --> 11:09.392
So how are you two doing?

11:09.560 --> 11:11.637
[NlLES AND DAPHNE CHUCKLE]

11:12.814 --> 11:15.567
Well, we're--
We're deliriously happy, of course.

11:15.776 --> 11:19.609
Although l-- l keep thinking about Mel
and how she must be feeling today.

11:19.781 --> 11:21.940
[CELL PHONE RlNGlNG]

11:22.618 --> 11:24.907
Poor Donny.
He must be devastated.

11:25.079 --> 11:27.156
- l'll never forgive myself for that.
NlLES: Hello?

11:27.332 --> 11:29.658
- Maybe l should go and see him.
- l wouldn't, Daph.

11:29.835 --> 11:32.956
You know, Donny and Mel
have suffered a terrible blow.

11:33.131 --> 11:36.715
They'll need space
and time to lick their wounds.

11:37.678 --> 11:40.431
Believe me,
the emotional state they're in,

11:40.599 --> 11:43.007
the last thing they'll want
is to speak with either of you.

11:43.227 --> 11:45.599
Frasier, could you hold it down?
lt's Mel.

11:46.773 --> 11:49.311
That woman never misses
an opportunity to show me up.

11:51.988 --> 11:53.648
Daphne, Simon's opening your gifts.

11:53.823 --> 11:55.448
Bloody hell.

11:55.659 --> 11:59.075
Simon, give me that. You idiot.

11:59.247 --> 12:01.453
Oh, Roz, you little snitch.

12:01.666 --> 12:03.493
You know, l'm starting
to have serious doubts

12:03.669 --> 12:07.169
about whether you're gonna be
the future mother of my children.

12:08.717 --> 12:11.469
Somewhere out there,
the future mother of your children

12:11.637 --> 12:14.674
just lifted her head
from a puddle of drool.

12:15.850 --> 12:17.049
[DOORBELL RlNGS]

12:17.227 --> 12:20.395
Yeah, but l bet
she's got a ripper body.

12:22.776 --> 12:23.855
- Daphne Moon?
- Yes?

12:24.027 --> 12:25.486
- These are for you.
- Oh, goodness.

12:25.654 --> 12:27.778
And so is this.
Consider yourself served.

12:27.949 --> 12:29.443
What?

12:29.617 --> 12:32.074
Well, you won't believe this.

12:32.246 --> 12:34.073
Mel insists on seeing me.

12:34.790 --> 12:37.626
Wow. Wonderful flowers.
Who are they from?

12:37.794 --> 12:42.422
Well, l can't read the card from here,
but l'd say they're from Donny.

12:42.592 --> 12:45.677
- He trying to get you back?
- Oh, he's getting me back, all right.

12:45.846 --> 12:48.337
- He's suing me.
NlLES: What?

12:48.516 --> 12:50.260
Call me crazy,

12:50.435 --> 12:53.140
but you know what l think
we all need right now?

12:53.355 --> 12:55.313
A nice pot of fondue.

12:57.485 --> 13:00.570
l'm sure l've seen one
in here somewhere.

13:05.537 --> 13:07.411
[KNOCKS]

13:07.664 --> 13:09.207
[DOOR OPENS]

13:10.376 --> 13:12.168
FRASlER:
Donny? Are you in here?

13:13.171 --> 13:14.832
DONNY:
Hi, Fras.

13:15.382 --> 13:16.793
FRASlER:
lt's kind of dark in here.

13:16.968 --> 13:18.961
Do you think maybe
we could turn on the light?

13:19.137 --> 13:21.213
- Okay.
- Okay.

13:22.433 --> 13:25.007
There, that's better. Heh-heh.

13:29.274 --> 13:30.650
Uh...

13:31.652 --> 13:33.147
Donny?

13:34.155 --> 13:36.481
You're gonna have to turn around.
l can't see you.

13:36.658 --> 13:38.616
DONNY:
We can't see you either.

13:40.955 --> 13:42.035
We?

13:42.249 --> 13:44.871
DONNY: Oh, that's right.
You haven't met my little friend.

13:45.044 --> 13:48.045
You remember him?
From the top of the wedding cake?

13:49.424 --> 13:51.750
l call him Mr. Chump.

13:51.927 --> 13:54.633
Say hello to Mr. Chump.

13:54.848 --> 13:56.841
- Oh, well, Donny, l don't--
- l said, say hello!

14:00.855 --> 14:03.976
Hello, Mr. Chump.

14:05.694 --> 14:07.522
- Donny, are you all right?
- Oh, yeah.

14:07.739 --> 14:09.317
l was not feeling very well yesterday,

14:09.491 --> 14:12.243
but the doctor gave me a few pills
and l'm feeling much better now.

14:12.411 --> 14:14.404
So, what can l do for you?

14:14.622 --> 14:18.122
Well, before l get to that, Donny,
l'd like you to know that my visit here

14:18.293 --> 14:19.704
was completely my own idea.

14:19.879 --> 14:22.548
Daphne has nothing to do with it.

14:23.216 --> 14:28.045
What happened to you yesterday
was unforgivable and devastating.

14:28.264 --> 14:29.462
l know whereof l speak.

14:29.641 --> 14:34.553
See, l too,
was once abandoned at the altar.

14:35.022 --> 14:39.566
You're feeling angry and hurt
and completely alone.

14:39.778 --> 14:41.937
Aren't you forgetting someone?

14:43.491 --> 14:46.030
Just so we're clear,

14:46.203 --> 14:49.204
all my remarks refer
to human relationships.

14:49.749 --> 14:53.332
Now, Daphne realizes you went
to great expense for this wedding,

14:53.503 --> 14:57.336
and she is prepared
to repay you over time.

14:57.550 --> 15:02.546
But, Donny, this $1 00,000 in punitive
damages for emotional distress,

15:02.723 --> 15:04.716
that is not you.

15:04.892 --> 15:06.767
That's not the Donny Douglas
l know.

15:08.689 --> 15:10.231
- lt's not?
- No.

15:10.775 --> 15:12.934
You don't want to sue Daphne.

15:14.070 --> 15:16.644
l'm a lawyer. lt's my natural impulse.

15:18.075 --> 15:20.318
Well, you know, maybe
l am being too hard on Daphne.

15:20.495 --> 15:22.987
ln all fairness,
she's not totally to blame.

15:23.207 --> 15:26.161
Gosh, there's plenty of blame
to go around.

15:27.128 --> 15:31.209
l mean, even l played a minor part
in these events.

15:33.678 --> 15:36.514
You? l was talking about me.

15:36.723 --> 15:39.891
Well, you, me, everyone.

15:40.061 --> 15:43.146
Let he who is without sin, right?

15:44.650 --> 15:46.643
Anyway, glad we had this talk.
God bless.

15:46.819 --> 15:49.393
Wait, wait, wait. Just a minute.

15:49.614 --> 15:52.236
What minor part did you play?

15:52.451 --> 15:55.157
l may have mentioned in passing
to Niles and Daphne

15:55.330 --> 15:58.201
how they felt about each other.

15:58.417 --> 16:02.498
Which may have conceivably set

16:03.089 --> 16:06.044
this whole thing in motion, perhaps.

16:07.178 --> 16:08.886
You did this on my wedding day?

16:09.097 --> 16:10.841
Oh, no. No, Donny, no.

16:11.057 --> 16:13.181
lt was the night before, but...

16:14.145 --> 16:16.387
What l'm saying is that
if you feel the urge to yell,

16:16.564 --> 16:17.679
then yell at me.

16:17.858 --> 16:20.812
lf you want to take a swing
at somebody, then here's my chin.

16:21.028 --> 16:23.021
Are you gonna hit me?

16:24.282 --> 16:26.489
Oh, yeah, l'm gonna hit you.

16:26.660 --> 16:28.452
l'm gonna hit you
with tortious interference

16:28.621 --> 16:31.112
and intentionally negligent infliction
of emotional distress.

16:31.291 --> 16:33.996
ln layman's terms,
l'm gonna sue your ass off.

16:34.211 --> 16:37.462
Me? But-- But Daphne's the one
who left you at the altar.

16:37.632 --> 16:40.550
That's right. That's why l'm suing her
for breach of contract.

16:41.136 --> 16:43.129
Listen, you're just being
emotional right now.

16:43.306 --> 16:46.177
Give this a few days
and l'm sure you'll feel much better.

16:46.393 --> 16:48.220
Actually, l'm feeling a lot better,
thank you.

16:48.395 --> 16:50.223
Suing you is just the tonic
that l needed.

16:50.773 --> 16:53.265
You know what else? l'm starving.
l haven't eaten in 24 hours.

16:53.443 --> 16:56.813
l'd ask you to join me,
but you should be saving your money.

16:57.615 --> 16:59.988
Turn the lights out when you leave.

17:00.410 --> 17:02.699
Oh, by the way, Fras.

17:03.414 --> 17:05.952
Who's Mr. Chump now?

17:09.964 --> 17:11.162
Where is Mel?

17:11.339 --> 17:13.748
That woman is punctual to a fault.
This is a bad sign.

17:13.926 --> 17:15.172
She's only five minutes late.

17:15.387 --> 17:18.138
Five? l thought it was two.

17:18.766 --> 17:21.768
She's doing this intentionally.
She's playing mind games.

17:21.936 --> 17:23.846
She's hoping to undermine
my confidence

17:24.022 --> 17:25.565
so she'll have the advantage.

17:25.775 --> 17:27.055
Yeah, but you're showing her.

17:27.902 --> 17:30.311
l'm sorry l'm late.
What's wrong with Niles?

17:30.489 --> 17:32.114
Oh, he's in a tizzy
because Mel's late.

17:32.325 --> 17:33.523
Dear God, she's never late.

17:33.743 --> 17:35.119
[NlLES GASPlNG]

17:35.286 --> 17:36.485
Steady, Niles.

17:36.663 --> 17:38.740
Nice job, Frasier.

17:38.958 --> 17:40.583
So how did things go with Donny?

17:40.793 --> 17:42.454
l used every psychological trick
in my bag

17:42.629 --> 17:44.088
to get myself added to the lawsuit.

17:44.256 --> 17:46.332
NlLES: That's unforgivable.
- Tell me about it.

17:46.509 --> 17:47.884
NlLES:
No, that prune Danish

17:48.052 --> 17:51.552
that Dad dropped down here
last Thursday is still here.

17:52.266 --> 17:55.552
- Oh, l think l see Mel pulling in.
NlLES: Don't panic. Oh!

17:55.728 --> 17:58.054
Thanks for the moral support.
Don't let her see you here.

17:58.231 --> 18:00.604
- lf you need us, we'll be right up there.
- Thanks.

18:06.116 --> 18:07.445
Hello, Mel.

18:07.994 --> 18:09.274
Niles.

18:10.079 --> 18:11.622
Please.

18:17.130 --> 18:19.966
Well, here we are,

18:20.175 --> 18:22.963
our four-day anniversary.

18:23.846 --> 18:26.172
- Mel, l never meant to--
- What, hurt me?

18:26.391 --> 18:27.471
lf that were the case,

18:27.643 --> 18:30.847
you never would have run off
with your little maid-whore

18:31.022 --> 18:34.143
leaving me holding the brochures
to our honeymoon.

18:34.735 --> 18:36.395
Technically,
she's a physical therapist.

18:39.032 --> 18:41.523
- You were saying?
- lf you think that l--

18:41.702 --> 18:45.487
- Oh, Mel. Here, here.
- No!

18:48.877 --> 18:52.294
l promised myself l wouldn't cry.
Damn it.

18:54.176 --> 18:56.714
l want you to listen to me
very carefully.

18:56.929 --> 18:59.385
Last night, as l lay in bed, awake,

18:59.557 --> 19:04.470
l thought l'm either going to kill you
or l'm going to kill myself.

19:04.981 --> 19:06.772
Well, here you are,
so l guess that leaves--

19:06.941 --> 19:08.566
MEL:
Will you shut up and let me finish?

19:08.735 --> 19:10.859
l realised that wouldn't
solve anything.

19:11.030 --> 19:13.901
So l've decided to make this
as painless as possible.

19:14.075 --> 19:17.694
You will have your divorce, Niles,
and it will be quick and clean.

19:17.872 --> 19:18.986
That's very generous.

19:19.165 --> 19:21.205
Hold your applause.
There are some conditions.

19:21.751 --> 19:23.246
As you know,
l have a certain standing

19:23.420 --> 19:25.330
in my social circle
that's important to me.

19:25.506 --> 19:29.801
And having my husband of three days
run off with some Cockney tart

19:29.970 --> 19:31.844
is a humiliation l'd prefer to avoid.

19:32.056 --> 19:34.844
- Yes, l understand completely.
- Here's how this is gonna play out.

19:35.059 --> 19:36.139
For the next few weeks,

19:36.311 --> 19:38.138
as far as the rest of the world
is concerned,

19:38.313 --> 19:40.353
- we're still happily married.
- Check.

19:40.524 --> 19:43.230
We will appear together in public
at various social occasions.

19:43.445 --> 19:44.725
- Check.
- ln private,

19:44.947 --> 19:46.192
l don't wanna lay eyes on you.

19:46.407 --> 19:47.605
Check, check.

19:47.783 --> 19:52.446
And when a suitable amount of time
has passed, l will file for divorce.

19:53.499 --> 19:56.916
Well, it seems like
you've thought of everything.

19:57.128 --> 20:00.498
l have. Here's the watch l was
going to give you as a wedding gift.

20:01.050 --> 20:02.877
Please wear it when we're together.

20:03.469 --> 20:05.094
lt's, uh...

20:05.263 --> 20:07.387
Yes, it said ''Forever yours'', l--

20:07.558 --> 20:10.513
l scratched it out with a screwdriver.

20:12.647 --> 20:15.186
There's something else
crudely carved here.

20:15.359 --> 20:19.939
Ah. Well, at least you were able to use
that F from ''forever.''

20:22.243 --> 20:23.903
Maybe it's not gonna be
so bad after all.

20:24.078 --> 20:25.656
She just gave him a watch.

20:25.830 --> 20:28.536
lsn't this all too typical?

20:28.709 --> 20:30.998
Niles leaves his wife
for another woman, he gets a gift.

20:31.170 --> 20:34.421
l try to do the right thing,
l get Mr. Chump and a lawsuit.

20:36.010 --> 20:38.133
Frasier, l know you thought
it was for the best,

20:38.304 --> 20:40.878
but l told you not to go see Donny,
didn't l?

20:41.058 --> 20:42.137
Yes, you did.

20:42.309 --> 20:44.433
- But you went down there, didn't you?
- Yes, l did.

20:44.604 --> 20:46.395
l told you not to screw around
with lawyers.

20:46.564 --> 20:48.059
All right, Dad.

20:48.483 --> 20:51.022
- l told him not to go down there.
- Will you shut up?

20:51.904 --> 20:53.897
All right, there she goes.

20:55.868 --> 20:57.528
So, Niles?

20:57.703 --> 21:01.120
Well, um, all things considered,
not so bad.

21:01.333 --> 21:03.456
ln exchange for a neat
and tidy divorce,

21:03.627 --> 21:06.083
all l have to do
is play the doting husband

21:06.255 --> 21:09.957
at some social functions
for a few weeks.

21:10.177 --> 21:11.506
Well, that doesn't sound so bad.

21:11.720 --> 21:13.180
What kind of social functions?

21:13.347 --> 21:17.809
Well, for instance,
tonight is our wedding reception.

21:18.938 --> 21:20.266
FRASlER:
Dear God.

21:20.481 --> 21:23.768
Well, since we eloped,
some of Mel's colleagues

21:23.944 --> 21:28.358
decided to throw a little last-minute
get-together to toast our nuptials.

21:28.533 --> 21:30.906
Well, after Donny gets
through with Frasier,

21:31.078 --> 21:34.412
you won't be the only one having
your nuptials toasted.

21:39.797 --> 21:41.505
Explain to me again
how you and Mel

21:41.674 --> 21:43.916
masquerading as husband and wife
is a good thing?

21:44.094 --> 21:46.882
- Well--
- lf l may, Daphne,

21:47.097 --> 21:49.007
it's basically to give Mel
a little wiggle room

21:49.183 --> 21:51.640
so she can get out this debacle
with her dignity intact.

21:51.853 --> 21:53.893
Well, what about Niles's dignity?

21:54.106 --> 21:56.432
Well, Maris got that in the divorce.
Ha-ha! Sorry, Niles.

21:56.651 --> 21:57.730
<i>[MOUTHS]
That's funny.</i>

21:57.902 --> 22:00.192
- Would you like some sherry?
- Yes, thanks.

22:00.364 --> 22:01.906
FRASlER: Daphne?
- Yeah, all right,

22:02.074 --> 22:04.566
l'll get your precious wedge of brie
and your water crackers.

22:04.744 --> 22:07.699
No. l meant,
would you like some sherry?

22:07.915 --> 22:09.160
Oh.

22:09.333 --> 22:10.744
Love some. Thanks.

22:12.379 --> 22:14.336
Listen, Daphne,
l know this is all very awkward,

22:14.506 --> 22:16.499
but if it speeds up
the divorce process,

22:16.676 --> 22:19.250
avoids the misery l went through
with Maris, isn't it worth it?

22:19.429 --> 22:20.592
Well...

22:20.806 --> 22:23.344
Come on, snookums, we can
get through this. What do you say?

22:23.559 --> 22:25.932
What did you just call me?

22:27.105 --> 22:28.814
- Snookums.
- Snookums?

22:28.982 --> 22:31.106
lt was an attempt at a pet name.

22:31.319 --> 22:34.404
Well, if it's all the same to you,
could we keep looking?

22:35.073 --> 22:38.858
Absolutely.
There's no rush whatsoever, truffles.

22:40.747 --> 22:43.036
lt's the chocolate, not the fungus.

22:44.752 --> 22:46.330
- lt's a work in progress.
- Yes.

22:46.504 --> 22:48.129
FRASlER: Here you are.
- Thank you.

22:48.298 --> 22:50.421
- Well, for you.
- Thank you.

22:50.593 --> 22:52.633
Here is to better days.

22:53.513 --> 22:56.301
For all of us. Ha-ha-ha-ho.

22:57.267 --> 22:58.466
Why, what happened to you?

22:58.644 --> 23:01.183
Well, l went down
and talked to Donny,

23:01.356 --> 23:04.108
try to convince him to drop
his lawsuit against you.

23:04.276 --> 23:06.565
lnstead, he's now suing me
as well for the part l played

23:06.737 --> 23:07.900
in getting you two together.

23:08.072 --> 23:09.864
DAPHNE:
Well, l am so sorry, Dr. Crane.

23:10.075 --> 23:12.401
This is turning
into such a horrible mess.

23:12.578 --> 23:15.330
Not that l expected it to be
a bed of roses, mind you,

23:15.498 --> 23:17.657
but it's gotten so you wonder
what God-awful calamity

23:17.834 --> 23:19.412
is gonna befall us next.

23:23.967 --> 23:27.503
Something smells in your elevator.

23:28.514 --> 23:32.299
Ohh. Now it smells in here too.

23:32.770 --> 23:36.768
l'm beginning to think this is not such
a ritzy building after all.

23:38.944 --> 23:40.902
Did you get my wedding gifts
down to the post?

23:41.113 --> 23:43.984
As we speak, they are winging
their way towards their rightful owners.

23:44.200 --> 23:45.695
Thank you, Simon.

23:45.911 --> 23:47.405
And in a totally unrelated matter,

23:47.580 --> 23:50.784
l am pleased to announce
that the Winnebago

23:50.959 --> 23:54.044
is now equipped
with a state-of-the-art DVD

23:54.213 --> 23:57.547
complete with surround sound.

23:57.759 --> 23:59.467
l don't believe this.

23:59.678 --> 24:01.338
<i>Tonight's feature is Braveheart</i>

24:01.513 --> 24:05.559
starring Australia's favourite son,
Mr. Mel Gibson.

24:05.727 --> 24:09.061
Showtime is at 8 sharp.
Everyone is invited.

24:09.273 --> 24:11.765
As tempting as that sounds,
l have a date.

24:11.943 --> 24:13.936
Niles is taking me to dinner
and dancing.

24:14.112 --> 24:16.070
At least this day will end
on a high note.

24:16.240 --> 24:18.233
l guess l can't avoid telling you this
any longer.

24:18.409 --> 24:22.740
l just want you to know l'm attending
this wedding reception under protest.

24:22.957 --> 24:26.042
- Wedding reception?
- Thanks, Dad.

24:26.211 --> 24:28.370
You know those social obligations
l was talking about?

24:28.547 --> 24:29.626
One of them is tonight.

24:29.798 --> 24:31.838
A wedding reception
for you and Mel?

24:32.009 --> 24:33.718
lt's-- lt's at the Equestrian Center.

24:33.928 --> 24:35.553
lt's nothing major.
lt's very impromptu.

24:35.722 --> 24:38.641
Champagne, cake, we pet the horses,
we're out of there by 1 1 .

24:39.310 --> 24:41.517
- Well, what about--?
- Gosh, Niles, look at the time.

24:41.688 --> 24:43.765
Sorry, but we've gotta
get across town in an hour.

24:43.941 --> 24:45.400
You better get home
and get changed.

24:45.568 --> 24:47.477
Don't forget to wear
that watch Mel gave you.

24:47.654 --> 24:50.192
- Watch?
- Thanks again, Dad.

24:50.407 --> 24:53.907
l can explain that.
l can explain everything tomorrow.

24:54.120 --> 24:55.200
lt's just a 24-hour delay.

24:55.372 --> 24:57.863
l switched all the reservations,
dining, dancing, everything.

24:58.042 --> 25:01.625
l promise l will make it up to you,
pooky.

25:02.088 --> 25:03.287
Even l hate that one.

25:07.136 --> 25:08.797
But what about our date?

25:08.972 --> 25:13.386
Oh, there, there, there, Daphne,
don't cry, don't cry.

25:13.561 --> 25:15.103
lt's all right.

25:15.271 --> 25:18.973
<i>This sounds like a job
for Braveheart.</i>

25:23.740 --> 25:26.196
[CLASSlCAL MUSlC PLAYlNG]

25:26.368 --> 25:28.527
MARTlN: Don't look now,
but there's a guy in a bow tie

25:28.704 --> 25:31.659
who's been checking me out
for the last 20 minutes.

25:32.668 --> 25:35.455
Oh, one of Mel's colleagues.
l met him earlier.

25:35.630 --> 25:37.005
What's he keep staring at me for?

25:37.173 --> 25:39.712
Well, he's a plastic surgeon.

25:40.886 --> 25:43.841
Maybe he's looking at your eyelids
and planning his next trip to Maui.

25:44.516 --> 25:47.007
[NlLES LAUGHlNG]

25:48.145 --> 25:51.349
Good Lord, look at him overacting.

25:51.566 --> 25:54.022
Trying to convince everybody
he's happily married.

25:54.194 --> 25:56.520
Have you ever seen anything
so pathetic in your life?

25:56.739 --> 25:58.697
How about you and Lilith?

26:00.076 --> 26:02.319
lt was a rhetorical question.

26:02.538 --> 26:03.617
Thank you.

26:03.789 --> 26:06.577
Niles, l'd like you to meet
Adrianna Pettibone.

26:06.751 --> 26:09.504
- Hello.
- Adrianna stables General Prescott,

26:09.713 --> 26:12.501
our current grand champion,
right here at the equestrian club.

26:12.675 --> 26:13.755
Wonderful.

26:13.927 --> 26:16.929
Speaking of grand champions,
how about this little filly, mm? Huh?

26:18.224 --> 26:20.798
l didn't even have
to check her teeth. Oh!

26:20.977 --> 26:22.805
[NlLES LAUGHlNG]

26:24.023 --> 26:27.190
- What are you doing?
- l'm sorry. l'm a little nervous.

26:27.736 --> 26:29.361
Well, l'm here.

26:29.530 --> 26:33.279
Congratulations and all that B.S.
Where's the bar?

26:33.451 --> 26:34.732
Roz, what are you doing here?

26:34.953 --> 26:37.623
l invited her. Your side of the guest list
looked a little sparse.

26:37.790 --> 26:41.871
Forgive me if l'm not in the spirit
of this wink-wink ''happy occasion,''

26:42.045 --> 26:45.047
- but l'm in a very crappy mood.
- Are you limping?

26:45.216 --> 26:48.217
Yeah, l twisted my ankle on the stairs.
You know how that happened?

26:48.428 --> 26:51.098
l couldn't find shoes,
so l had to wear these 3-inch spikes,

26:51.265 --> 26:53.803
and the ''check engine'' light
on my dash keeps coming on.

26:54.018 --> 26:55.429
What does that have to do with it?

26:55.603 --> 26:57.347
Nothing. lt just really ticks me off.

26:57.522 --> 26:59.931
The bar! The bar! Thank you.

27:02.779 --> 27:07.608
- That was so sweet of her to come.
- Niles, this is important.

27:07.785 --> 27:09.862
lf anyone should ask
about the honeymoon,

27:10.080 --> 27:11.242
we're flying to Paris,

27:11.415 --> 27:13.657
then we're taking
the Orient Express to Venice,

27:13.834 --> 27:17.085
where we'll spend two weeks
at the Mansarda Palazetto Suite

27:17.255 --> 27:19.248
at the Cipriani.

27:20.301 --> 27:21.760
What's the matter?

27:23.555 --> 27:25.014
lt sounds like a wonderful trip.

27:25.223 --> 27:28.759
- lt's not my fault we're not going.
- l know.

27:29.020 --> 27:31.227
Ah. Here's the happy couple.

27:31.398 --> 27:35.099
All right, you two,
show me those pearly whites.

27:36.779 --> 27:40.908
- All right, now, how about a kiss?
- Well, l hardly know you, but... Ha-ha!

27:44.581 --> 27:46.241
He's kidding.

27:47.167 --> 27:48.745
Here we go. Mm.

27:48.919 --> 27:52.289
Come on, doc.
This is your wife, not mine.

27:53.133 --> 27:55.589
- All right, well.
- Okay.

27:55.928 --> 27:57.506
CROWD:
Ohh.

27:57.722 --> 27:59.762
[CROWD APPLAUDS]

28:00.141 --> 28:01.422
- Thank you.
- Thanks.

28:02.186 --> 28:04.642
l'll go check on dad and Frasier.

28:05.189 --> 28:07.182
- Yes, they do make a lovely couple.
- Don't they?

28:07.359 --> 28:10.479
l'm sure they'll be happy together
for many years.

28:10.654 --> 28:12.944
Well, you never know.

28:14.451 --> 28:17.025
- Dad?
- Well, you don't, do you?

28:17.204 --> 28:19.530
l mean,
l'm just saying you never know.

28:19.749 --> 28:22.323
No, l guess you don't.

28:22.502 --> 28:25.172
Been lovely talking with you.
Enjoy the party.

28:25.381 --> 28:27.339
What the hell's wrong with you?

28:28.426 --> 28:31.096
ln a few weeks,
l'm gonna look like a genius.

28:33.474 --> 28:36.144
Well, l feel really stupid.
l just came on to the guy in the tux.

28:36.311 --> 28:38.185
They really should make waiters
wear nametags.

28:38.397 --> 28:40.474
Yes, Roz, carrying trays
and taking drink orders

28:40.650 --> 28:42.061
leaves so much room for ambiguity.

28:42.277 --> 28:43.985
Shut up.

28:44.154 --> 28:47.524
l think it's going pretty well, don't you?
Do you think anyone's suspicious?

28:47.742 --> 28:51.076
No, it's the greatest phoney reception
l've ever been to.

28:51.246 --> 28:52.409
So how are you holding up?

28:52.623 --> 28:55.031
lf l have to stretch my muscles
into a smile one more time,

28:55.209 --> 28:56.289
l think my face may crack.

28:56.461 --> 28:58.419
MEL: Niles.
- Yes, darling!

29:00.883 --> 29:04.217
lt's time to cut the cake, so why
don't you just gather everyone around?

29:04.387 --> 29:06.096
- Okay.
- All right.

29:06.265 --> 29:09.017
Excuse me, l'm sorry, l need
to borrow Frasier for just one moment.

29:09.185 --> 29:10.929
Oh, sure.

29:12.606 --> 29:16.687
Uh, Frasier, l had an interesting little
phone call from Donny this afternoon.

29:16.861 --> 29:17.893
- Oh?
- Yes.

29:18.071 --> 29:21.026
He said you'd been by
to see him earlier today.

29:21.575 --> 29:22.774
l may have done so.

29:22.952 --> 29:26.073
Yes, he said you were a busy little bee
before the wedding,

29:26.248 --> 29:29.415
first buzzing in Niles's ear and then
you were buzzing in Daphne's ears--

29:29.585 --> 29:31.578
- Let me explain. Now, you see--
- Buzz, buzz...

29:31.755 --> 29:33.379
Now-- Now please--

29:33.548 --> 29:34.960
Just stop that, please!

29:35.175 --> 29:37.465
You see, l've been torturing myself
trying to figure out

29:37.637 --> 29:39.630
how this all happened so quickly,
and now l know.

29:39.806 --> 29:41.764
l won't forget this.

29:43.060 --> 29:46.430
- What was that all about?
- Donny talked to Mel.

29:47.065 --> 29:49.557
- Told you not to go down there.
- Oh, Dad, stop it!

29:49.735 --> 29:50.980
MEL:
Attention, everyone.

29:51.154 --> 29:54.523
Before we cut the cake,
Niles's brother Frasier

29:54.741 --> 29:57.909
would like to make a toast
in our honour.

29:58.120 --> 30:00.327
l didn't know you were doing this.

30:00.749 --> 30:02.540
Neither did l.

30:04.295 --> 30:05.493
Well, uh...

30:06.840 --> 30:08.500
Love...

30:11.470 --> 30:14.757
...is an awesome force.

30:15.684 --> 30:18.258
lt can make us do things
we never imagined were possible.

30:18.896 --> 30:22.847
For you see,
we don't actually choose love.

30:23.026 --> 30:24.735
lt chooses us.

30:24.904 --> 30:29.234
And once it has, we are powerless
to do anything about it.

30:31.286 --> 30:34.039
Ladies and gentlemen,
raise your glasses with me

30:34.248 --> 30:38.496
in toasting my brother
and the love of his life,

30:39.088 --> 30:41.247
for she is truly the woman
of his dreams.

30:41.466 --> 30:45.334
And my father and l couldn't be
more thrilled with his choice.

30:45.888 --> 30:47.347
To the happy couple.

30:47.598 --> 30:49.591
[CROWD CHATTERS]

30:50.518 --> 30:55.265
Well, wasn't that clever
of your brother?

30:55.441 --> 30:57.648
lt's only too bad
your little English muffin

30:57.819 --> 30:59.777
wasn't here to enjoy it as well.

30:59.947 --> 31:01.276
Which reminds me,

31:01.449 --> 31:05.364
you do realise that
while we are pretending to be married,

31:05.537 --> 31:08.989
you absolutely cannot be seen
in public with Daphne.

31:10.877 --> 31:14.745
- l--
- l love you too, honey.

31:26.646 --> 31:28.058
Hello?

31:29.525 --> 31:31.684
Hello, is anybody home?

31:31.903 --> 31:34.608
MARTlN: Hey, Simon.
Just making coffee. You want some?

31:34.823 --> 31:40.115
l was thinking of something colder
with a bit more of an amber hue.

31:40.872 --> 31:43.660
MARTlN: Beer?
- Brilliant!

31:44.043 --> 31:45.870
lf you aren't the finest detective
in Seattle,

31:46.045 --> 31:48.881
l am the prince of Wales.

31:49.049 --> 31:51.588
MARTlN:
How did Eddie like his walk?

31:57.643 --> 32:00.348
The little nipper loved it.

32:01.314 --> 32:05.147
Oh, l think nature's calling him again.
His bladder's worse than mine.

32:05.319 --> 32:07.893
l'll be back in a flash.

32:08.073 --> 32:09.651
MARTlN:
Okay.

32:09.866 --> 32:11.326
Was that Simon's voice l heard?

32:11.535 --> 32:13.279
Yeah, he just took Eddie
on a walk for me.

32:13.496 --> 32:15.904
Well, about time that chowderhead
made himself useful.

32:16.082 --> 32:18.621
Oh, don't be so hard on him.
He tries.

32:18.794 --> 32:19.993
[DOORBELL RlNGS]

32:20.171 --> 32:23.790
Yes, well, if you're talking about
my patience, he certainly does.

32:26.095 --> 32:27.969
- Ah. Niles, come on in.
- Frasier.

32:28.139 --> 32:30.465
Oh, hey, Dad, about a block
from here l saw a dog

32:30.642 --> 32:34.142
that looked remarkably like Eddie
tied up outside a bar.

32:34.856 --> 32:37.015
- lmpossible. He was just here.
NlLES: Oh.

32:39.153 --> 32:41.312
So, uh, did you say anything to her?

32:41.489 --> 32:42.983
No, no, you told us not to.

32:43.199 --> 32:44.480
Want us out of here?

32:44.659 --> 32:46.985
No, l think l'll be safer
with witnesses.

32:47.204 --> 32:50.289
- Niles, l didn't hear you come in.
- l just got here.

32:50.458 --> 32:52.535
DAPHNE: Hey.
- Hey.

32:55.756 --> 32:57.750
- How are you today?
- Wonderful.

32:57.926 --> 33:00.299
l realised that postponing
our date one day

33:00.471 --> 33:03.638
doesn't really amount to much
in the great scheme of things.

33:03.808 --> 33:08.056
- So how was your wedding reception?
- Oh, it was your average night in hell.

33:08.981 --> 33:11.140
Well, that's behind us now.

33:11.317 --> 33:13.856
We have a wonderful evening
to look forward to.

33:14.029 --> 33:15.227
l bought a new dress.

33:15.406 --> 33:17.944
lt's much too expensive,
but you're worth it.

33:18.159 --> 33:20.485
And l'm getting my hair done
and my--

33:21.497 --> 33:24.035
Why are you looking
at each other like that?

33:25.084 --> 33:26.828
We're not looking
at each other like that.

33:27.003 --> 33:28.249
Like what? Like anything.

33:28.422 --> 33:29.703
MARTlN: Uh-uh.
DAPHNE: Yes, you were.

33:29.882 --> 33:32.634
Those darty little glances
mean something's up. Niles?

33:32.802 --> 33:35.376
- About tonight--
- l hate the way this is starting.

33:35.597 --> 33:40.557
Mel feels that as long as she and l
are acting like we're married,

33:41.229 --> 33:44.101
you and l can't be seen together
in public.

33:44.275 --> 33:46.434
- So that means--
- l know what that means.

33:46.653 --> 33:47.816
lt's just until the divorce.

33:47.988 --> 33:49.566
- Whenever that bloody is.
- Daphne--

33:49.740 --> 33:52.492
lf you'll excuse me,
l have a splitting headache.

33:52.660 --> 33:54.902
NlLES: You know, if you look at it
from Mel's point of view,

33:55.080 --> 33:56.539
it really does make a lot of sense.

33:59.293 --> 34:01.452
He came so close.

34:02.005 --> 34:05.754
- What did you say?
- l said, ''Damn that Mel.''

34:08.596 --> 34:11.384
No, you didn't.
You should have, but you didn't.

34:11.558 --> 34:13.635
Sounded to me
like you were taking her side.

34:13.811 --> 34:15.888
All right, could we turn
the clock back two minutes

34:16.063 --> 34:17.688
and pretend this never happened?

34:17.900 --> 34:20.391
Why don't we just turn it back
to 1 0 minutes before my wedding

34:20.570 --> 34:22.194
and save everybody all this trouble?

34:22.362 --> 34:24.937
NlLES: What are you saying?
- What do you think l'm saying?

34:25.159 --> 34:27.781
Sounds like you're saying
you're sorry you did this.

34:27.995 --> 34:29.870
- Maybe that's what l'm saying.
- Oh, boy.

34:30.081 --> 34:31.909
Before anybody
says something they'll regret--

34:32.083 --> 34:35.335
Butt out! lf you hadn't opened your
mouth, we wouldn't be in this mess.

34:35.545 --> 34:37.753
Donny wouldn't be suing me
and everyone else in sight.

34:37.924 --> 34:39.585
And l wouldn't be out
two weeks' salary

34:39.760 --> 34:42.512
for a new dress
l'm apparently never going to wear.

34:42.722 --> 34:45.558
And you wouldn't be kowtowing
to that shrew of a wife of yours.

34:45.766 --> 34:49.303
- This is all my fault?
- Oh, shut up, Frasier.

34:50.982 --> 34:53.308
The only thing more hollow
than your protest of innocence

34:53.485 --> 34:54.813
is your big, fat head!

34:56.697 --> 34:59.699
l am wounded!

35:01.161 --> 35:03.867
l intervened only out of love and caring
about the two people--

35:04.082 --> 35:05.909
Oh, put a sock in it.

35:06.084 --> 35:09.335
l am sick of listening to you yammering
on about everything under the sun.

35:09.547 --> 35:11.540
- Daphne--
- And l'm sick of listening to you too.

35:11.716 --> 35:14.208
You got anything to say, old man?

35:14.428 --> 35:15.839
Good!

35:19.476 --> 35:20.970
[DOOR SLAMS]

35:26.234 --> 35:28.061
l'm waiting.

35:30.573 --> 35:32.032
For what?

35:32.241 --> 35:37.948
An apology for that unprovoked
broadside you levelled at me.

35:38.958 --> 35:41.532
You expect me to apologise to you?

35:41.753 --> 35:44.209
Expect it, sir, and demand it.

35:44.423 --> 35:47.627
Well, then here's my answer. No!

35:47.802 --> 35:49.297
- No?
- No!

35:50.013 --> 35:54.427
And furthermore, why don't you take
your broadside, stuff it in a chair

35:54.602 --> 35:59.265
and keep your unlimited supply
of opinions, suggestions, proposals

35:59.442 --> 36:01.185
and recommendations to yourself.

36:01.402 --> 36:03.941
- Well, l never.
- No, you always.

36:04.156 --> 36:05.235
Get out!

36:10.747 --> 36:13.500
How's a corned beef sandwich
sound?

36:14.961 --> 36:16.788
l am appalled.

36:17.005 --> 36:19.793
Well, no problem. There's some
smoked turkey in here too.

36:26.266 --> 36:27.891
What is my offence?

36:28.978 --> 36:32.015
What egregious sin
have l committed

36:32.232 --> 36:34.688
that l should be so maligned?

36:35.361 --> 36:39.146
Was l to just sit idly by
and watch these two misguided souls

36:39.324 --> 36:42.030
embark on doomed relationships?

36:42.203 --> 36:44.955
Would they have thanked me
for that?

36:45.707 --> 36:48.459
- Not very likely, l dare say.
- Who moved the mustard?

36:48.669 --> 36:50.995
- Top shelf, door.
- Bingo.

36:51.172 --> 36:56.131
And then, when they were perched
on the very brink of disaster,

36:56.679 --> 36:58.672
l snatched them
from the gaping maw

36:58.848 --> 37:02.300
and placed them gently
into one another's arms.

37:02.520 --> 37:04.678
But am l accorded a hero's welcome
for my troubles?

37:04.897 --> 37:07.567
Am l hoisted on their shoulders
and paraded about the room?

37:07.734 --> 37:09.858
l don't have my glasses.
What's the expiration date?

37:10.070 --> 37:11.185
Last week.

37:11.405 --> 37:12.865
l'll chance it.

37:13.408 --> 37:14.867
No.

37:15.077 --> 37:18.778
Those two ingrates
turn on me like vipers

37:18.956 --> 37:21.329
and make me the villain
of the piece.

37:21.877 --> 37:23.336
Well, hear me now.

37:23.545 --> 37:28.458
From this day forward, Frasier Crane
will not interfere with those two.

37:29.177 --> 37:32.630
<i>This is it. Finished. Finito.</i>

37:32.807 --> 37:35.381
[SPEAKS lN LATlN]

37:35.602 --> 37:37.310
MARTlN: Uh-huh.
- l know l've made

37:37.479 --> 37:41.015
declarations like this before, but l tell
you what, Dad, you mark the calendar.

37:41.234 --> 37:43.690
You note the time on your watch.

37:43.904 --> 37:48.650
This is it.

37:49.411 --> 37:51.700
Well, if you figure out a way
to get them back together,

37:51.872 --> 37:53.497
l'll be in my room
if you need any help.

37:53.666 --> 37:54.911
Have you been listening to me?

37:55.084 --> 37:58.537
MARTlN: Well, l tried not to,
but some of it still got through.

38:07.141 --> 38:08.256
Hello, Dr. Crane.

38:10.186 --> 38:11.811
Daphne.

38:12.481 --> 38:16.100
- Making yourself a sandwich?
- No, Dad did.

38:16.277 --> 38:19.065
Hope he didn't use the mayonnaise.
l meant to throw it out.

38:19.281 --> 38:22.117
- l've seen him eat worse.
- l'll say.

38:22.326 --> 38:25.530
Remember when he dropped
his hot dog at the petting zoo?

38:27.625 --> 38:30.911
Oh, Dr. Crane, l'm so sorry
l said those things about you.

38:31.087 --> 38:32.202
l didn't mean them.

38:32.422 --> 38:34.629
Oh, l know, Daphne. Come here.

38:36.219 --> 38:38.212
l guess this all finally came
crashing down on me.

38:38.388 --> 38:41.805
Yes, l know.
lt's perfectly understandable.

38:41.976 --> 38:44.763
Listen, l know you can't go out
on your date with Niles tonight,

38:44.938 --> 38:47.809
but what's to stop two friends
from going out to dinner?

38:48.025 --> 38:51.062
My treat. You can even wear
that new dress of yours.

38:51.237 --> 38:52.317
DAPHNE:
Thank you.

38:52.530 --> 38:56.315
That's a lovely offer,
but l think l'll just stay home tonight.

38:56.494 --> 38:57.739
Have a quiet night.

38:57.954 --> 39:00.742
- l understand.
- Thank you.

39:02.126 --> 39:04.831
- Sure you won't change your mind?
- Positive.

39:05.588 --> 39:07.415
Hello.

39:07.591 --> 39:12.337
My furry friend and l have just
concluded our daily constitutional,

39:12.555 --> 39:17.135
with young Edward here dropping
a few amendments along the way.

39:18.813 --> 39:20.770
So, what's on the docket tonight?

39:20.982 --> 39:22.975
All l want is a quiet night at home.

39:23.151 --> 39:25.857
Oh, Stilts,
you and l are of one mind.

39:26.030 --> 39:28.652
l'll hoist a beer
while you get dinner started

39:28.825 --> 39:32.409
and then when our bellies are full
and you've done the dishes,

39:32.580 --> 39:37.658
we will adjourn to the Winnebago
where Mr. Jean-Claude Van Damme,

39:37.836 --> 39:43.674
<i>the Muscles from Brussels, will ply
his trade against the forces of evil.</i>

39:44.219 --> 39:46.177
- Ready at 8?
- Make it 7:30.

39:49.351 --> 39:50.679
NlLES:
Good idea, Dad.

39:50.852 --> 39:52.845
An evening out, just the two of us.

39:53.022 --> 39:55.181
l had no idea you enjoyed
the Natural History Museum.

39:55.358 --> 39:58.360
Oh, sure, and that documentary on
the rain forest is supposed to be great.

39:58.529 --> 39:59.774
That's what l hear.

39:59.989 --> 40:02.860
Hope it has Pygmies. l like Pygmies.

40:03.702 --> 40:05.576
l know you do.

40:05.787 --> 40:07.448
So, uh, where's--?

40:07.665 --> 40:09.824
She went out with Frasier
to a restaurant for dinner.

40:10.335 --> 40:11.877
Ah.

40:12.045 --> 40:14.833
- Did she happen to ask about--?
- Sorry.

40:21.766 --> 40:22.845
Dad, we're going up.

40:23.017 --> 40:25.259
Oh, God. Oh, l'm sorry.

40:25.478 --> 40:28.052
Well, we'll just have to take
the long way.

40:30.318 --> 40:32.644
Why do you like Pygmies so much?

40:34.782 --> 40:37.902
They're short and they blow darts.
What's not to like?

40:40.956 --> 40:42.285
Come on. Come on up here.

40:42.458 --> 40:45.128
NlLES: What could possibly be
so important for me to see up here?

40:45.295 --> 40:47.288
The guy in 1 708
got some homing pigeons.

40:47.464 --> 40:48.840
He built a coop up here for them.

40:49.008 --> 40:53.386
Pigeons? l don't like pigeons.
They have no respect for public art.

40:54.264 --> 40:56.056
Trust me. You're gonna like this.

40:56.225 --> 40:58.597
Dad, l don't think l handled things
very well today.

40:58.770 --> 41:01.557
Do you think Daphne
will ever forgive me?

41:01.857 --> 41:04.229
Why don't you ask her for yourself?

41:12.662 --> 41:14.869
Your table is ready, sir.

41:17.835 --> 41:20.505
- You look stunning.
- Thank you.

41:20.672 --> 41:22.795
You look dashing.

41:23.133 --> 41:25.707
FRASlER:
l trust this will be to your liking.

41:25.886 --> 41:28.343
Everything's to my liking.

41:28.556 --> 41:31.130
Looks like we're having
that first date after all.

41:31.351 --> 41:33.309
You went to so much trouble.

41:33.521 --> 41:35.680
lt wasn't me. lt was your brother.

41:35.899 --> 41:39.019
Well, you know me. l hate to butt in.

41:39.194 --> 41:40.570
NlLES:
Ohh...

41:41.823 --> 41:46.700
l'd planned to take Daphne to dinner
when suddenly inspiration struck.

41:46.871 --> 41:49.445
Since you two couldn't go
to Au Pied de Cochon this evening,

41:49.624 --> 41:53.243
my faithful companion and l

41:53.462 --> 41:55.586
would bring it to you courtesy
of their caterer.

41:55.798 --> 41:58.717
lf dancing at the Starlight Room
was impossible,

41:58.885 --> 42:00.629
we'd give you the real thing.

42:03.308 --> 42:05.016
lt's all so overwhelming.

42:05.227 --> 42:07.516
Yeah. Frasier, Dad,
l don't know what to say.

42:07.730 --> 42:10.268
You even got that man
to move his pigeons.

42:12.027 --> 42:13.569
There were no pigeons.

42:13.904 --> 42:15.447
Ohh.

42:16.157 --> 42:17.486
How can we ever thank you two?

42:17.659 --> 42:19.284
Just have a beautiful evening.

42:19.453 --> 42:21.077
l think we can do that.

42:21.288 --> 42:24.574
- And, Frasier, listen--
- Apology accepted, Niles.

42:25.293 --> 42:27.867
Oh, just remember to give
the lingonberry sauce a little stir--

42:28.088 --> 42:30.046
MARTlN:
They can figure it out.

42:30.716 --> 42:32.294
Right.

42:37.642 --> 42:40.762
- Daphne, about today--
- Let's just forget about that.

42:40.937 --> 42:42.349
Why don't we start from here?

42:42.564 --> 42:44.641
l would love that.

42:45.485 --> 42:48.190
- To us.
- To us.

43:01.755 --> 43:04.377
l'm usually so nervous
on a first date,

43:04.550 --> 43:06.543
but not tonight.

43:07.846 --> 43:09.221
Would you like to dance?

43:09.431 --> 43:10.925
Oh, l'd love to.

43:22.948 --> 43:24.573
So where are you from?

43:24.741 --> 43:27.529
- Manchester, England.
- Oh, my.

43:27.703 --> 43:29.862
- Big family?
- Hideously.

43:30.040 --> 43:31.415
[NlLES CHUCKLES]

43:31.583 --> 43:32.663
DAPHNE:
And you?

43:32.835 --> 43:34.958
l'm from a small mountain village
in Tibet.

43:35.129 --> 43:36.375
[DAPHNE CHUCKLlNG]

43:36.548 --> 43:39.549
Tenzing Norgay used
to carry me to school.

43:39.718 --> 43:42.257
You know what
l've always wondered?

43:42.430 --> 43:44.756
- Think l can guess?
- Yeah.

